#1 Resected colon adenocarcinoma (T2, N0, M0)
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Paul service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Ruiz, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
We are not recommending adjuvant chemotherapy in this situation.  Therefore, I will not make followup arrangements for Ms. Mingo to return in the outpatient setting.  I will ask Dr. Ruiz to visit with her prior to hospital dismissal for formal treatment recommendations.  Certainly if the need arises in the future, I will be more than happy to help facilitate care.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

